  "text": "The present findings of a decreased renal blood flow during moderate hypothermia confirm previous results [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In the present study pretreatment with hexamethonium abolished the down regulation of renal blood flow in hypothermia, suggesting that the nervous system is involved in this response. However the results are somewhat ambiguous since the hexamethonium treated normothermic rats show a decreased blood flow at a level comparable with the saline treated hypothermic animals without attaining statistical significance.",
